cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new graph convolutional neural network model for learning branch-and-bound variable selection policies for combinatorial optimization problems. This involves training the model via imitation learning from an expert rule and demonstrating its effectiveness on a series of hard problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization problems, which suggests the sub-categories cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as possible choices.
